<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="129" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="129">
Biennial (or perennial?) herb. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Sterile stems</emphasis>
absent. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Rosette</emphasis>
present during florescence; rosette leaves alternate, broadly obovate, base attenuated and shortly spurred, 0.5-1.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.4-0.7 cm. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Flowering stems</emphasis>
1 to 3 (-4), erect, slender, 3-7 cm; single stems shoot from rosette centers, others shoot from the rosette leaf axils; lateral proximal leaves sometimes opposite, akin to rosette leaves but smaller, 0.6-0.8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.3-0.5 cm, base shortly spurred; distal leaves alternate, spatulate-obovate to spatulate-oblanceolate, 0.7-1.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.3-0.4 cm, apex obtuse, base shortly spurred. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Cymes</emphasis>
scorpioid, 2 to 3 branched; branches 1 to 2 flowered; bracts obliquely oblanceolate, apex obtuse, 4-9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-4 mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Sepals</emphasis>
5, lanceolate-oblong, subequal, ca. 2 mm, base shortly spurred, apex obtuse. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Petals</emphasis>
5, yellow, broadly lanceolate, ca. 4 mm, apex mucronate. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Stamens</emphasis>
10; antesepalous one ca. 3 mm; antepetalous one inserted ca. 1 mm above petal base, slightly shorter than the antesepalous stamens. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Nectar scales</emphasis>
broadly cuneate, ca. 0.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.4 mm, apex truncate. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Carpels</emphasis>
erect, lanceolate, ca. 3.5 mm, base connate for ca. 1 mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Styles</emphasis>
slender, ca. 1 mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Follicles</emphasis>
stellately divergent at maturity. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Seeds</emphasis>
oblong, ca. 0.6 mm, papillate.
</paragraph>
