<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="130">
<pageBreakToken pageId="5" pageNumber="130" start="start">Distribution</pageBreakToken>
and habitat.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="130">
At this time, based on our field observations, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. B. Zhang, D. Tan &amp; R. X. Wei" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sedum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sedum lipingense" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lipingense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">Sedum lipingense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known to occur in Longxi village, Mengyan town, Liping County, Guizhou Province. It grows on moist limestone rocks, at ca. 800 m altitude, in groups of several hundred individuals.
</paragraph>
